title.narrative: STRENGTHEN PARTNERS CAPACITY (GOV. & CSOS) FOR CHILD FRIENDLY EQUITABLE EDUCATION

description.narrative: By 2022, education officers at national and sub-national levels have increased capacity to plan, budget, implement and monitor child friendly education in elementary and primary schools including education for out of school children in selected provinces., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, school aged girls and boy, especially the most marginalized, successfully complete pre-primary and primary education.

description.narrative: In the midst of COVID-19, several milestones were achieved in the Education Sector: The National Education Plan (NEP) 2020-2029 as a basic education sector plan was officially launched in June 2021; the roll-out of ECE expansion underway as part of the 1-6-6 restructuring; the Behaviour Management Policy launched in July 2021 and its implementation underway to promote eliminating violence against women and girls in schools and communities; education sector coordination mechanisms further strengthen with the successful application submission for the GPE’s System Capacity Grant for PNG. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:28/12/2021
